      <p>Re-coding transactions is the visible part of a cleanup; rebuilding a broken structure is the part that actually makes the numbers trustworthy. The work is clearing Opening Balance Equity to the right accounts without distorting equity, consolidating a sprawling chart of accounts down to one clean structure, reconciling every balance-sheet account &mdash; loans, cash, receivables, payables &mdash; back to reality, fixing item and product mappings so they post where they should, and then verifying that the balance sheet and profit-and-loss tie before the file is called CPA-ready. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; we fix the structure, and your CPA confirms the tax impact because we don&rsquo;t file taxes.</p>
